article.description: — Ben Shungu registered 12 points and six rebounds as Vermont topped UMass Lowell 62-53 on Tuesday.
article.headline: Shungu, Smith carry Vermont over UMass-Lowell 62-53
article.linkText: Shungu, Smith carry Vermont over UMass-Lowell 62-53
article.story: LOWELL, Mass. -- — Ben Shungu registered 12 points and six rebounds as Vermont topped UMass Lowell 62-53 on Tuesday. Stef Smith added 10 points for Vermont (1-1, 1-1 America East Conference), and Bailey Patella chipped in nine points. Obadiah Noel had 18 points for the River Hawks (2-4, 1-1). Ron Mitchell added 15 points and Connor Withers had 11 rebounds. The Catamounts evened the season series against the River Hawks with the win. UMass Lowell defeated Vermont 73-65 Monday. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
